gtf2gff3 comes from http://www.sequenceontology.org

gffTypeFix.pl is written locally.

The initial script comes very close to producing gff3 
that gbrowse is happy with, but a little extra processing 
is done to handle the rest.

There are two prerequisite steps. 

1) Build the chromosome length files, so far 
this has just been done by hand with a text editor.

2) Unload everything from ZFIN needed to build the files:

% dbaccess <dbname> unload_clone_lengths.sql
% dbaccess <dbname> unload_marker_names.sql
% dbaccess <dbname> unload_zdb_ids.sql


Finally, here's how I've used these scripts so far:

% ./gtf2gff3 --cfg gtf2gff3.cfg vega.gtf > vega.unprocessed.gff3 && ./gffTypeFix.pl vega vega_chromosome_lengths.txt vega.unprocessed.gff3 vega.gff3

% ./convertAssemblyToGff.pl vega assembly_for_tom.tab vega_assembly.gff3 full_length_clones.gff3

% ./gtf2gff3 --cfg gtf2gff3.cfg ensembl.gtf > ensembl.unprocessed.gff3 && ./gffTypeFix.pl ensembl ensembl_chromosome_lengths.txt ensembl.unprocessed.gff3 ensembl.gff3 

